              "uco-observable:stringValue": "Query Reports Utilities Help Log Out\n\nAPPEAL,CLOSED\n\nU.S. District Court\nWestern District of Missouri (Jefferson City)\nCRIMINAL DOCKET FOR CASE #: 2:22-cr-04065-BCW All Defendants\n\nCase title: USA v. Perry et al Date Filed: 10/18/2022\n\nMagistrate judge case numbers: 2:22-mj-03026-WJE Date Terminated: 08/27/2025\n2:22-mj-03027-WJE\n\nAssigned to: Chief District Judge Brian C Wimes\nReferred to: Magistrate Judge Willie J. Epps, Jr\nAppeals court case number: 25-2763 Eighth Circuit Court of\nAppeals\n\nDefendant (1)\nBryan C. Perry represented by Bryan C. Perry\nTERMINATED: 08/27/2025 25753-510\nCANAAN U.S. PENITENTIARY\nInmate Mail/Parcels\nP.O. Box 300\nWAYMART, PA 18472\nPRO SE\n\nThomas J. Kirsch\nKirsch & Kirsch, LLC\n214 E. McCarty St.\nSuite A\nJefferson City, MO 65101\n573-222-0324\nEmail: tj@kk-attorneys.com\nLEAD ATTORNEY\nATTORNEY TO BE NOTICED\nDesignation: CJA Appointment\n\nBenjamin J. Gray\nPO Box 717\nKirksville, MO 63501\n(660) 627-3840\nFax: (888) 807-5645\nEmail: bgray@kirksvilleattorney.com\nTERMINATED: 06/01/2023\nDesignation: CJA Appointment\n\nPending Counts Disposition\nASSAULTING/RESISTING/IMPEDING\nOFFICERS/EMPLOYEES Dismissed on Government Motion\n(1)\n18:111.F ASSAULTING/RESISTING/IMPEDING\nOFFICERS/EMPLOYEES Dismissed on Government Motion\n(1s)\nCONSPIRACY TO MURDER\nDismissed on Government Motion\n(1ss)\nDefendant is hereby committed to the BOP for Life on Count\n1sss; 5 years on Count 2sss; 6 years on Count 3sss; 20 years on\nCounts 4ss, 5ss, 6ss, 7ss, 8ss, 9ss, 10ss, 11ss, 12ss, 13ss, 14ss,\n15ss, 16ss, 17ss, and 18ss; 8 years on Counts 19ss and 20ss; 10\nyears on Count 35ss; 15 years on Counts 36ss; 3 years on Count\n39ss; and 5 years on Count 41ss; all counts to run concurrently\nwith each other, for a total of Life. Additionally, on Counts\n21ss, 22ss, 23ss, 24ss, 25ss, 26ss, 27ss, 28ss, 29ss, 30ss, 31ss,\n18:1117.F CONSPIRACY TO MURDER 32ss, 33ss, and 34ss, a term of Life is imposed on each count, to\n(1sss) be served consecutively to each other and consecutively to all\nother counts, for a total term of imprisonment of Life. TSR: 5\nyears on each of Counts 1sss, 21ss, 22ss, 23ss, 24ss, 25ss, 26ss,\n27ss, 28ss, 29ss, 30ss, 31ss, 32ss, 33ss, and 34ss; 3 years on\nCounts 2sss, 3sss, 4ss, 5ss, 6ss, 7ss, 8ss, 9ss, 10ss, 11ss, 12ss,\n13ss, 14ss, 15ss, 16ss, 17ss, 18ss, 19ss, 20ss, 35ss, and 36ss;\nand 1 year on Count 39ss; each count to run concurrently with\neach other, for a total of 5 years. SA: $3,800; No Fine;\nRestitution: $3,717.98.\nUNLAWFUL TRANSPORT OF FIREARMS, ETC.\nDismissed on Government Motion\n(2)\n18:922G.F UNLAWFUL TRANSPORT OF FIREARMS, ETC.\nDismissed on Government Motion\n(2s)\nCONSPIRACY TO DEFRAUD THE UNITED STATES\nDismissed on Government Motion\n(2ss)\nDefendant is hereby committed to the BOP for Life on Count\n1sss; 5 years on Count 2sss; 6 years on Count 3sss; 20 years on\nCounts 4ss, 5ss, 6ss, 7ss, 8ss, 9ss, 10ss, 11ss, 12ss, 13ss, 14ss,\n15ss, 16ss, 17ss, and 18ss; 8 years on Counts 19ss and 20ss; 10\nyears on Count 35ss; 15 years on Counts 36ss; 3 years on Count\n39ss; and 5 years on Count 41ss; all counts to run concurrently\nwith each other, for a total of Life. Additionally, on Counts\n21ss, 22ss, 23ss, 24ss, 25ss, 26ss, 27ss, 28ss, 29ss, 30ss, 31ss,\n18:371.F CONSPIRACY TO DEFRAUD THE UNITED\n32ss, 33ss, and 34ss, a term of Life is imposed on each count, to\nSTATES\nbe served consecutively to each other and consecutively to all\n(2sss)\nother counts, for a total term of imprisonment of Life. TSR: 5\nyears on each of Counts 1sss, 21ss, 22ss, 23ss, 24ss, 25ss, 26ss,\n27ss, 28ss, 29ss, 30ss, 31ss, 32ss, 33ss, and 34ss; 3 years on\nCounts 2sss, 3sss, 4ss, 5ss, 6ss, 7ss, 8ss, 9ss, 10ss, 11ss, 12ss,\n13ss, 14ss, 15ss, 16ss, 17ss, 18ss, 19ss, 20ss, 35ss, and 36ss;\nand 1 year on Count 39ss; each count to run concurrently with\neach other, for a total of 5 years. SA: $3,800; No Fine;\nRestitution: $3,717.98.\nVIOLENT CRIME/DRUGS/MACHINE GUN\nDismissed on Government Motion\n(3)\n18:924C.F VIOLENT CRIME/DRUGS/MACHINE GUN\nDismissed on Government Motion\n(3s)\nCONSPIRE TO IMPEDE OR INJURE OFFICER\nDismissed on Government Motion\n(3ss)\nDefendant is hereby committed to the BOP for Life on Count\n1sss; 5 years on Count 2sss; 6 years on Count 3sss; 20 years on\nCounts 4ss, 5ss, 6ss, 7ss, 8ss, 9ss, 10ss, 11ss, 12ss, 13ss, 14ss,\n15ss, 16ss, 17ss, and 18ss; 8 years on Counts 19ss and 20ss; 10\nyears on Count 35ss; 15 years on Counts 36ss; 3 years on Count\n39ss; and 5 years on Count 41ss; all counts to run concurrently\nwith each other, for a total of Life. Additionally, on Counts\n21ss, 22ss, 23ss, 24ss, 25ss, 26ss, 27ss, 28ss, 29ss, 30ss, 31ss,\n18:372.F CONSPIRE TO IMPEDE OR INJURE OFFICER 32ss, 33ss, and 34ss, a term of Life is imposed on each count, to\n(3sss) be served consecutively to each other and consecutively to all\nother counts, for a total term of imprisonment of Life. TSR: 5\nyears on each of Counts 1sss, 21ss, 22ss, 23ss, 24ss, 25ss, 26ss,\n27ss, 28ss, 29ss, 30ss, 31ss, 32ss, 33ss, and 34ss; 3 years on\nCounts 2sss, 3sss, 4ss, 5ss, 6ss, 7ss, 8ss, 9ss, 10ss, 11ss, 12ss,\n13ss, 14ss, 15ss, 16ss, 17ss, 18ss, 19ss, 20ss, 35ss, and 36ss;\nand 1 year on Count 39ss; each count to run concurrently with\neach other, for a total of 5 years. SA: $3,800; No Fine;\nRestitution: $3,717.98.\nPROTECTION OF OFFICERS AND EMPLOYEES OF U.S.\nDismissed on Government Motion\n(4s-10s)\nDefendant is hereby committed to the BOP for Life on Count\n1sss; 5 years on Count 2sss; 6 years on Count 3sss; 20 years on\nCounts 4ss, 5ss, 6ss, 7ss, 8ss, 9ss, 10ss, 11ss, 12ss, 13ss, 14ss,\n15ss, 16ss, 17ss, and 18ss; 8 years on Counts 19ss and 20ss; 10\nyears on Count 35ss; 15 years on Counts 36ss; 3 years on Count\n39ss; and 5 years on Count 41ss; all counts to run concurrently\nwith each other, for a total of Life. Additionally, on Counts\n21ss, 22ss, 23ss, 24ss, 25ss, 26ss, 27ss, 28ss, 29ss, 30ss, 31ss,\n18