danger\nto the community. The Court grants the government's motion to detain and remands defendant to the custody of the U.S. Marshal pending\nfurther order of the Court. Written Order forthcoming.\n\nCounsel appearing for USA: Randy Eggert and Michael Oliver. Counsel appearing for Defendant: Katie Wang. Pretrial/Probation Officer:\nLance Jordan. Time in court: 1:30 pm to 2:36 pm. To order a transcript of this hearing please contact Angel Geiser, 573-556-7564. This is\na TEXT ONLY ENTRY. No document is attached. (Geiser, Angel) [2:22-mj-03026-WJE] (Entered: 10/13/2022)\n10/13/2022 13 GOVERNMENT'S EXHIBIT INDEX. (Geiser, Angel) [2:22-mj-03026-WJE] (Entered: 10/13/2022)\n10/13/2022 14 DEFENDANT'S EXHIBIT INDEX as to Jonathan S. O'Dell. (Geiser, Angel) [2:22-mj-03026-WJE] (Entered: 10/13/2022)\n10/13/2022 10 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Magistrate Judge Willie J. Epps, Jr: PRELIMINARY HEARING as to Bryan C. Perry held on\n10/13/2022. Defendant present, in custody, ready to proceed. Parties stipulate to the affidavit attached to the complaint as being the direct\ntestimony of Agent McPheeters; report accepted and entered by the Court. Government tenders the affidavit as evidence. Agent\nMcPheeters called to testify. Objections ruled as stated on the record. After receiving evidence and hearing arguments, the Court finds\nAgent McPheeters' testimony reliable and determines that probable cause is established; defendant bound over to U.S. District Court for\nfurther proceedings.\n\nDETENTION HEARING as to Bryan C. Perry held on 10/13/2022. Defendant makes corrections to the Pretrial Services Report. Parties\nmake proffer. Parties stipulate to factual contents of Pretrial Services Report as being the direct testimony of Pretrial Services Officer.\nGovernment offers exhibits. Arguments presented. Based upon the evidence heard and the information provided in the Pretrial Services\nReport, the Court finds that there are no set of conditions that can be entered to e