granting motion to continue 60 as to Jonathan S. O'Dell (2). Accelerated Jury Trial as to Bryan C. Perry and Jonathan S. O'Dell\nset for 10/21/2024 08:00 AM in Courtroom 4B, Jefferson City (VDJJC) before District Judge Stephen R. Bough. Pretrial Conference as to\nBryan C. Perry and Jonathan S. O'Dell set for 9/24/2024 02:00 PM in Courtroom 3A, Jefferson City (WJE) before Chief Magistrate Judge\nWillie J. Epps, Jr. Absent extraordinary circumstances, no further continuances shall be granted. Signed on 2/26/2024 by Chief\nMagistrate Judge Willie J. Epps, Jr. (McIntosh, Michal-Ane) (Entered: 02/26/2024)\n03/20/2024 62 PRO SE MOTION for release of Brady materials by Bryan C. Perry. Suggestions in opposition/response due by 4/3/2024 unless otherwise\ndirected by the court. (Attachments: # 1 Envelope)(Geiser, Angel) (Entered: 03/20/2024)\n03/20/2024 63 ORDER denying 62 pro se motion for release of Brady materials as to Bryan C. Perry (1). Defendant is represented by counsel. As a\nresult, Defendant must address the Court through his attorney. If defense counsel feels that relief is warranted, he or she shall file the\nappropriate motion. Signed on 3/20/2024 by Chief Magistrate Judge Willie J. Epps, Jr. This is a TEXT ONLY ENTRY. No document is\nattached. (McIntosh, Michal-Ane) (Entered: 03/20/2024)\n05/31/2024 64 NOTICE OF HEARING as to Bryan C. Perry. This is the official notice for this hearing. Status Conference set for 6/6/2024 02:30 PM in\nCourtroom 3A, Jefferson City (WJE) before Chief Magistrate Judge Willie J. Epps, Jr. Only defendant and defense counsel requested to\nappear. Signed on 05/31/2024 by Chief Magistrate Judge Willie J. Epps, Jr. This is a TEXT ONLY ENTRY. No document is attached.\n(Geiser, Angel) (Entered: 05/31/2024)\n06/04/2024 65 ***AMENDED NOTICE OF HEARING as to Bryan C. Perry. This is the official notice for this hearing. Status Conference re-set for\n6/6/2024 02:00 PM in Courtroom 3A, Jefferson City (WJE) before Chief Magistrate Judge Willie J. Epps, Jr.Signed on 06/04/2024 by\nChief Magistrate Judge Willie J. Epps, Jr. This is a change in time only. TEXT ONLY ENTRY. No document is attached. (Geiser, Angel)\n(Entered: 06/04/2024)\n06/06/2024 66 MOTION to seal document by Bryan C. Perry. Suggestions in opposition/response due by 6/20/2024 unless otherwise directed by the\ncourt. (Kirsch, Thomas) (Entered: 06/06/2024)\n06/06/2024 67 ORDER granting 66 motion to seal document as to Bryan C. Perry (1). Signed on 6/6/2024 by Chief Magistrate Judge Willie J. Epps, Jr.\n(McIntosh, Michal-Ane) (Entered: 06/06/2024)\n06/06/2024 68 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Chief Magistrate Judge Willie J. Epps, Jr: STATUS CONFERENCE as to Bryan C. Perry held\non 6/6/2024. Courtroom has been cleared for this proceeding. Defendant and counsel discuss issues on the record. Defendant and counsel\nnotify the Court the issue has been resolved. Thomas Kirsch will continue to represent the defendant in this matter. Defendant remains in\nthe custody of the US Marshal. Counsel appearing for Defendant: Thomas Kirsch. Time in court: 1:59 pm to 2:07 pm. To order a transcript\nof this hearing please contact Angel Geiser, 573-556-7564. This is a TEXT ONLY ENTRY. No document is attached. (Geiser, Angel)\n(Entered: 06/06/2024)\n08/15/2024 70 ADMINISTRATIVE TRANSFER as to Bryan C. Perry and Jonathan S. O'Dell. This is a change in Judge assignment only. Case\nreassigned to District Judge Brian C. Wimes for all further proceedings. District Judge Stephen R. Bough no longer assigned to case. This\ncase number shall now read: 2:22-cr-04065-BCW. This is a TEXT ONLY ENTRY. No document is attached. (Berner, Crystal) (Entered:\n08/15/2024)\n08/16/2024 Set/Reset Hearings as to Bryan C. Perry, Jonathan S. O'Dell: Pretrial Conference as to Bryan C. Perry, Jonathan S. O'Dell is set for\n9/24/2024 02:00 PM in Courtroom 3A, Jefferson City (WJE) before Chief Magistrate Judge Willie J. Epps, Jr. (Geiser, Angel) (Entered:\n08/16/2024)\n09/12/2024 73 MOTION to continue trial by Bryan C. Perry as to Bryan C. Perry, Jonathan S. O'Dell. Suggestions in opposition/response due by\n9/26/2024 unless otherwise directed by the court. (Kirsch, Thomas) (Entered: 09/12/2024)\n09/12/2024 74 ORDER denying motion to continue 73 as to Bryan C. Perry (1). Continuances are disfavored and should be granted only for a compelling\nreason. United States v. Wright, 682 F.3d 1088, 1090 (8th Cir. 2012) (citation omitted). Among the factors the Court considers in ruling on\nDefendant's motion to continue are: \"(1) the nature of the case and whether the parties have been allowed adequate timing for trial\npreparation; (2) the diligence of the party requesting the continuance; (3) the conduct of the opposing party and whether a lack of\ncooperation has contributed to the need for a continuance; (4) the effect of the continuance and whether a delay will seriously\ndisadvantage either party; and (5) the asserted need for the continuance, with weight to be given to sudden exigencies and unforeseen\ncircumstances.\" United States v. Cordy, 560 F.3d 808, 815-16 (8th Cir. 2009) (citation omitted).\n\nHere, after reviewing each factor, the Court denies Mr. Perry's motion. First, while this case does involve 41 pending counts against Mr.\nPerry, the third superseding indictment was filed in October 2023, almost 12 months ago (Doc. 48). Mr. Perry is currently in custody\nawaiting trial. (Doc. 10). Second, this is the fourth motion to continue in this case. (See Docs. 22, 43, 61). The last time the Court granted\na continuance, the Court noted that \"[a]bsent extraordinary circumstances, no further continuances shall be granted.\" (Doc. 61).\n\nThird, the Court has not been made aware of any improper conduct or lack of cooperation by the opposing party.\n\nFinally, the Court will address the fourth and fifth factors together. Here, the Court has not been made aware that any party would be\nseriously prejudiced by proceeding to trial on October 28, 2024. Further, the Court finds the requested need for the continuance\nunpersuasive. In his motion, counsel for Mr. Perry seeks additional time based on multiple conflicts, both professional and personal, that\nnecessitate a continuance.(Doc. 73). The Court finds that counsel has not identified any \"sudden exigencies and unforeseen\ncircumstances.\" Cordy, 560 F.3d at 815-16.\n\nBased on these observations, the Court concludes that this matter may proceed to trial on October 28, 2024, without affecting Mr. Perry's\nconstitutional rights.\n\nSigned on 9/12/24 by Chief Magistrate Judge Willie J. Epps, Jr. This is a TEXT ONLY ENTRY. No document is attached. (Blanton,\nDoraly) (Entered: 09/12/2024)\n09/19/2024 76 NOTICE OF HEARING as to Bryan C. Perry and Jonathan S. O'Dell. This is the official notice for this hearing. Pretrial Conference as to\nBryan C. Perry and Jonathan S. O'Dell is re-set for 9/27/2024 01:30 PM in Courtroom 3A, Jefferson City (WJE) before Chief Magistrate\nJudge Willie J. Epps, Jr. Signed on 09/19/2024 by Chief Magistrate Judge Willie J. Epps, Jr. This is a TEXT ONLY ENTRY. No document\nis attached. (Geiser, Angel) (Entered: 09/19/2024)\n09/20/2024 77 MOTION to continue trial by Bryan C. Perry as to Bryan C. Perry, Jonathan S. O'Dell. Suggestions in opposition/response due by\n10/4/2024 unless otherwise directed by the court. (Kirsch, Thomas) (Entered: 09/20/2024)\n09/20/2024 78 ORDER as to Bryan C. Perry 77 MOTION to continue trial filed by Bryan C. Perry. The Government is directed to respond to 77\nMOTION to continue trial on or before September 23, 2024, unless otherwise directed by the Court. Signed on 9/20/2024 by Chief\nMagistrate Judge Willie J. Epps, Jr. This is a TEXT ONLY ENTRY. No document is attached. (Blanton, Doraly) (Entered: 09/20/2024)\n09/23/2024 79 SUGGESTIONS in opposition by USA as to Bryan C. Perry, Jonathan S. O'Dell re 77 MOTION to continue trial . Reply suggestions due\nby 10/7/2024 unless otherwise directed by the court. (Clark, Casey) (Entered: 09/23/2024)\n09/23/2024 80 ORDER denying motion to continue 77 as to Bryan C. Perry (1). The Court finds defense counsel's reasoning does not rise to the level of\n\"extraordinary circumstances\" and therefore does not warrant an additional continuance. Signed on 9/23/2024 by Chief Magistrate Judge\nWillie J. Epps, Jr. This is a TEXT ONLY ENTRY. No document is attached. (Blanton, Doraly) (Entered: 09/23/2024)\n09/24/2024 Set/Reset Hearings as to Bryan C. Perry and Jonathan S. O'Dell. (Geiser, Angel) (Entered: 09/24/2024)\n09/27/2024 81 NOTICE OF HEARING as to Bryan C. Perry, Jonathan S. O'Dell. This is the official notice for this hearing.\n\nPretrial Conference by Telephone set for 10/10/2024 01:00 PM in Chambers before District Judge Brian C Wimes.\n\nSigned on 9/27/24 by District Judge Brian C Wimes. This is a TEXT ONLY ENTRY. No document is attached. (Diefenbach, Tracy)\nConference call information emailed to counsel. (Entered: 09/27/2024)\n09/27/2024 82 RULES OF TRIAL Signed on 9/27/24 by District Judge Brian C Wimes.(Diefenbach, Tracy) (Entered: 09/27/2024)\n09/27/2024 84 NOTICE of filing United States' Notice of Intention to Rely on Other Acts of a Similar Nature by USA as to Bryan C. Perry, Jonathan S.\nO'Dell (Turner, Ashley) (Entered: 09/27/2024)\n09/27/2024 85 NOTICE of filing United States' Notice of Expert Witness - Qulia by USA as to Bryan C. Perry, Jonathan S. O'Dell (Turner, Ashley)\n(Entered: 09/27/2024)\n09/27/2024 86 NOTICE of filing United States' Notice of Expert Witness - Amy Corrigan by USA as to Bryan C. Perry, Jonathan S. O'Dell (Attachments:\n# 1 Exhibit Government's Exhibit 1)(Turner, Ashley) (Entered: 09/27/2024)\n09/27/2024 87 NOTICE of filing United States' Notice of Expert Witness - Fox by USA as to Bryan C. Perry, Jonathan S. O'Dell (Turner, Ashley)\n(Entered: 09/27/2024)\n09/27/2024 88 NOTICE of filing United States' Notice of Expert Witness - Marsh by USA as to Bryan C. Perry, Jonathan S. O'Dell (Turner, Ashley)\n(Entered: 09/27/2024)\n09/27/2024 89 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Chief Magistrate Judge Willie J. Epps, Jr: PRETRIAL CONFERENCE as to Bryan C. Perry and\nJonathan S. O'Dell held on 9/27/2024. Parties present, ready to proceed. Government will have 48 witnesses and 120 exhibits. Defendant\nPerry will have 5 witnesses and 20 exhibits, and Defendant O'Dell will have 5 witnesses and 15 exhibits. Government is to file their\nwitness list no later than 10 days prior to trial and their exhibit list no later than 3 days prior to trial. Defense is to file their witness list no\nlater than 7 days prior to trial and their exhibit list no later than 3 days prior to trial. Stipulations and Motions in limine are due no later\nthan 7 days prior to trial. Proposed voir dire and jury instructions are due no later than 10 days prior to trial. Government instructed to\ndisclose any 404B issues 7 days prior to trial. Defendants will rely on the defense of general denial.\n\nMatter is currently set on the October 2024, joint criminal jury trial docket and is probable for trial. Trial is estimated to last 14 days.\nDefendants remain in custody of the US Marshal.\nGovernment informs the Court that they are ready for trial ; parties are directed to inform trial judge of date concerns. Defendants renew\nchallenges to the Court; Court denies request for continuance of this matter and notifies parties this matter will be set on October 28, 2024,\nfor jury trial. Court encourages parties to schedule a time to review the Court's technology.\n\nCounsel appearing for USA: Casey Clark and Ashley Turner. Counsel appearing for Defendant: Thomas Kirsch (Perry) and Jonathan\nTruesdale (O'Dell). Time in court: 1:30 pm to 2:10 pm. To order a transcript of this hearing please contact Angel Geiser, 573-556-7564.\nThis is a TEXT ONLY ENTRY. No document is attached. (Geiser, Angel) (Entered: 09/27/2024)\n\n09/27/2024 90 MOTION for leave to file Sealed Motion by USA as to Bryan C. Perry, J