ing please contact Denise Halasey, 816-512-5657,\ndenise_halasey@mow.uscourts.gov. (Diefenbach, Tracy) (Entered: 11/01/2024)\n11/01/2024 140 Minute Entry for proceedings held before District Judge Brian C Wimes: DAY 5 OF JURY TRIAL as to Bryan C. Perry, Jonathan S.\nO'Dell held on 11/1/2024. Time in court: 8:30 a.m. to 11:45 a.m.. To order a transcript of this hearing please contact Denise Halasey, 816-\n512-5657, denise_halasey@mow.uscourts.gov. (Diefenbach, Tracy) (Entered: 11/03/2024)\n11/04/2024 141 Minute Entry for proceedings held before District Judge Brian C Wimes: DAY SIX OF JURY TRIAL as to Bryan C. Perry, Jonathan S.\nO'Dell held on 11/4/2024. Time in court: 8:40 a.m. to 5:05 p.m.. To order a transcript of this hearing please contact Denise Halasey, 816-\n512-5657, denise_halasey@mow.uscourts.gov. (Diefenbach, Tracy) (Entered: 11/05/2024)\n11/05/2024 142 Minute Entry for proceedings held before District Judge Brian C Wimes: DAY 7 OF JURY TRIAL as to Bryan C. Perry and Jonathan S.\nO'Dell held on 11/5/2024. Time in court: 10:00 a.m. to 3:58 p.m.To order a transcript of this hearing please contact Denise Halasey, 816-\n512-5657, denise_halasey@mow.uscourts.gov. (Warren, Melissa) (Entered: 11/05/2024)\n11/06/2024 143 Minute Entry for proceedings held before District Judge Brian C. Wimes: DAY 8 OF JURY TRIAL as to Bryan C. Perry, Jonathan S.\nO'Dell held on 11/6/2024. Time in court: 8:35 a.m. to 1:26 p.m. To order a transcript of this hearing please contact Denise Halasey, 816-\n512-5657, denise_halasey@mow.uscourts.gov. (Moore, Terri) (Entered: 11/06/2024)\n11/07/2024 144 Minute Entry for proceedings held before District Judge Brian C Wimes:DAY 9 JURY TRIAL as to Bryan C. Perry & Jonathan S. O'Dell\nheld on 11/7/2024. Time in court: 8:36 a.m. to 4:50 p.m. To order a transcript of this hearing please contact Denise Halasey, 816-512-\n5657, denise_halasey@mow.uscourts.gov. (Lock, Tania) (Entered: 11/08/2024)\n11/07/2024 145 JURY INSTRUCTIONS given. (Lock, Tania) (Entered: 11/08/2024)\n11/07/2024 146 JURY NOTES as to Bryan C. Perry & Jonathan S. O'Dell. (Lock, Tania) (Entered: 11/08/2024)\n11/07/2024 147 GOVERNMENT'S EXHIBIT INDEX as to Bryan C. Perry & Jonathan S. O'Dell. (Lock, Tania) (Entered: 11/08/2024)\n11/07/2024 148 JURY VERDICT as to Bryan C. Perry (1) Guilty on Count 1-37, 39 and 41 of the third superseding indictment; and Not Guilty on Count\n40 of the third superseding indictment. (Lock, Tania) (Entered: 11/08/2024)\n11/07/2024 149 JURY VERDICT as to Jonathan S. O'Dell (2) Guilty on Count 1-35 and 43 of the third superseding indictment. (Lock, Tania) (Entered:\n11/08/2024)\n11/07/2024 150 ORDER as to Bryan C. Perry & Jonathan S. O'Dell. The Court hereby orders the Probation Office to complete a Presentence Investigation\nReport as to the above listed defendants. Signed on 11/07/2024 by District Judge Brian C Wimes. This is a TEXT ONLY ENTRY. No\ndocument is attached. (Lock, Tania) (Entered: 11/08/2024)\n11/12/2024 NOTICE OF HEARING CANCELLATION as to Bryan C. Perry, Jonathan S. O'Dell. The Accelerated Jury Trial set for the week of\n11/12/2024 is canceled. Signed on 11/12/24 by District Judge Brian C Wimes. This is a TEXT ONLY ENTRY. No document is attached.\n(Diefenbach, Tracy) For daily docket purposes only. No notice sent. (Entered: 11/12/2024)\n12/09/2024 152 PRO SE MOTION for new trial by Bryan C. Perry. Suggestions in opposition/response due by 12/23/2024 unless otherwise directed by\nthe court. (Attachments: # 1 Criminal Cover Sheet)(Kern, Kendra) (Entered: 12/09/2024)\n12/09/2024 153 ORDER denying 152 motion for new trial as to Bryan C. Perry (1). Defendant is represented by counsel. As a result, Defendant must\naddress the Court through his attorney. If defense counsel feels that relief is warranted, he or she shall file the appropriate motion. Signed\non 12/9/2024 by Chief Magistrate Judge Willie J. Epps, Jr. (Blanton, Doraly) (Entered: 12/09/2024)\n12/21/2024 154 MOTION for extension of time to file post-trial motions by Bryan C. Perry as to Bryan C. Perry, Jonathan S. O'Dell. Suggestions in\nopposition/response due by 1/6/2025 unless otherwise directed by the court. (Kirsch, Thomas) (Entered: 12/21/2024)\n12/21/2024 155 MOTION for extension of time to file post-trial motions by Jonathan S. O'Dell. Suggestions in opposition/response due by 1/6/2025\nunless otherwise directed by the court. (Truesdale, Jonathan) (Entered: 12/21/2024)\n12/23/2024 156 SUGGESTIONS in support by Bryan C. Perry re 154 MOTION for extension of time to file post-trial motions (Kirsch, Thomas) (Entered:\n12/23/2024)\n12/23/2024 157 SUGGESTIONS in support by Jonathan S. O'Dell re 155 MOTION for extension of time to file post-trial motions (Truesdale, Jonathan)\n(Entered: 12/23/2024)\n12/23/2024 158 ORDER granting 154 Defendant Bryan C. Perry's and 155 Defendant Jonathan S. O'Dell's motions for extension of time to file post-trial\nmotions. Defendants shall file their post-trial motions on or before January 2, 2025. This is a TEXT ONLY ENTRY. No document is\nattached. (Entered: 12/23/2024)\n12/23/2024 159 PRO SE MOTION for order requesting a mistrial and ineffective counsel by Bryan C. Perry. Suggestions in opposition/response due by\n1/6/2025 unless otherwise directed by the court. (Kern, Kendra) (Entered: 12/26/2024)\n12/30/2024 160 PRO SE MOTION for ineffective assistance of counsel by Bryan C. Perry. Suggestions in opposition/response due by 1/13/2025 unless\notherwise directed by the court. (Attachments: # 1 Envelope)(Melvin, Greg) (Entered: 12/30/2024)\n01/02/2025 161 MOTION for acquittal Pursuant to Rule 29 by Jonathan S. O'Dell. Suggestions in opposition/response due by 1/16/2025 unless otherwise\ndirected by the court. (Truesdale, Jonathan) (Entered: 01/02/2025)\n01/02/2025 162 MOTION for new trial by Bryan C. Perry. Suggestions in opposition/response due by 1/16/2025 unless otherwise directed by the court.\n(Kirsch, Thomas) (Entered: 01/02/2025)\n01/16/2025 163 MOTION for extension of time to file response/reply as to 162 MOTION for new trial by USA as to Bryan C. Perry. Suggestions in\nopposition/response due by 1/30/2025 unless otherwise directed by the court. (Clark, Casey) (Entered: 01/16/2025)\n01/16/2025 164 MOTION for extension of time to file response/reply as to 161 MOTION for acquittal Pursuant to Rule 29 by USA as to Jonathan S.\nO'Dell. Suggestions in opposition/response due by 1/30/2025 unless otherwise directed by the court. (Clark, Casey) (Entered: 01/16/2025)\n01/17/2025 165 ORDER granting 163 The Government's motion for extension of time to file response to Defendant Bryan C. Perry's motion for new trial.\nThe Government shall file its response on or before February 6, 2025. This is a TEXT ONLY ENTRY. No document is attached. (Entered:\n01/17/2025)\n01/17/2025 166 ORDER granting 164 The Government's motion for extension of time to file response to Defendant Jonathan S. O'Dell's Motion for\nJudgment of Acquittal, or in the Alternative, for a New Trial. The Government shall file its response on or before February 6, 2025. This is\na TEXT ONLY ENTRY. No document is attached. (Entered: 01/17/2025)\n01/17/2025 167 ORDER denying 159 motion for order requesting a mistrial and ineffective counsel as to Bryan C. Perry and 160 motion for ineffective\nassistance of counsel as to Bryan C. Perry. Defendant is represented by couns"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
